summary: I saw a comment on an article about Brock from Pokemon getting a love interest that basically said, "people are gonna complain...
body:
I saw a comment on an article about Brock from Pokemon getting a love interest that basically said, “people are gonna complain because it’s not LGBTQ representation, just you wait”

It seems like people boil down issues of LGBTQ representation to be “only happy if the character isn’t straight” but I’ve always felt like it was more of an issue of people being annoyed that straight has always been the default and people wish that other forms of character and relationship would appear.

This is compounded by the fact that many creators like to play with the idea of LGBTQ to attract the gay crowd while still defaulting the characters as straight (queerbaiting) or shoving in a straight romance to create tension when the charactars have no chemistry and no real reason to like each other

This doesnt mean that LGBTQ people are going to be mad at straight characters like Brock just because they’re straight. It would be a larger issue if a Brock had been teased as being queer and then ultimately the creators made him straight (cough cough Voltron cough)
